      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027ve updated the implementation to ensure the UI does not try to implement back-end \nsession management. Instead, the UI now properly handles loss of session reactively \nthrough existing error handling mechanisms.\n\nChanges made:\n- Removed all session management logic from the UI\n- Removed circular dependency (src/store/index.js ↔ UserManagementStore)\n- updateUser action is now pure - only updates user data\n- The UI will handle session invalidation reactively if it occurs\n\nThis eliminates timeouts, circular dependencies, and route change races.",
      "parentUuid": "5395bf91_2ed718ec",
      "range": {
