      "writtenOn": "2026-05-18T09:25:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "implemented the confirmation dialog with locale strings as you \nsuggested, with one adjustment to align with the architectural feedback:\n\nSince we removed all UI session management per comments #14, #26, and #162, I adjusted \nthe message to accurately reflect the actual behavior:\n\n**Message**: \"Are you sure you want to change the password for the logged-in user \n\u0027{user}\u0027? The new password will take effect on the next login.\"\n\n**Title**: \"Change Password\"\n\nThis provides user awareness about the sensitive operation without making false \npromises about forced logout (which the UI no longer performs). The message is \ntruthful about what actually happens: password is updated, session stays active \n(bmcweb behavior), new password works on next login.\n\nIf you prefer the message to say \"will be logged out\" for user clarity even though \nthe logout doesn\u0027t happen immediately, I\u0027m happy to adjust it. Please let me know \nyour preference.\n\n@jwestover@nvidia.com",
